@{FG Highlight}External macros only!@{FG Text}

Purpose: Gets the number of words in an article.

Syntax:  @{b}getarticlewordcount@{ub}
         [ARTICLE name/S | DOCUMENT name/S | WINDOW name/S | ARTICLEID number/I]

Format:  @{U}Parameter@{UU}  @{U}Values to enter@{UU}
         ARTICLE    is the name of the article. (Default=current)
         DOCUMENT   is the document name. (Default=current article)
         WINDOW     is the window name. (Default=current article)
         ARTICLEID  is the number of the article. (Default=current)

Result:  The number of words in the article is returned to the RESULT
         variable.

Example: getarticlewordcount
         numwords=RESULT

         getarticlewordcount article 'Story1'
         numwords=RESULT

@{" Command Format     " link PageStream3:Help/PGS.MSU/FORM}
@{" Article ID numbers " link PageStream3:Help/PGS.MSU/IDNU}
