@{U}@{FG Highlight}GETDRAWINGDISPLAY                                                           @{FG Text}@{UU}

@{FG Highlight}External macros only!@{FG Text}

Purpose: Gets the drawing display status.

Syntax:  @{b}getdrawingdisplay@{ub} [WINDOW name/S]

Format:  @{U}Parameter@{UU}  @{U}Values to enter@{UU}
         WINDOW     is the window name. (Default=current)

Result:  Returns the drawing display status <ON|OFF> to RESULT.

Example: getdrawingdisplay   /* will print the drawing display status to the output console */
         say 'Drawing Display: '||result

@{" Command Format    " link PageStream3:Help/PGS.MSU/FORM}
